<TITLE> Hands folded, teacher seeks BCL pardon </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 30 (bdnews24.com) -- Pro-government Banagladesh Chhatra League has forced a Jagannath University teacher to apologise with folded hands for urging student organisations to coexist peacefully on the campus. Baktiar Rana, the marketing department head, at a meeting on May 26 asked the BCL, opposition BNP-backed Jatiyatabadi Chhatra Dal and pro-Jamaat-e-Islami Islami Chhatra Shibir to share the campus in peace. Witnesses said Kamrul Hassan Ripon, the BCL's president of the university unit, who was also present at the meeting, protested at his comments regarding Shibir and demanded that he withdrew it. On Sunday, Ripon, flanked by other BCL leaders and supporters, again asked Rana to beg pardon. "He begged forgiveness following demands from the activists," Ripon told bdnews24.com. "When asked to retract his comments, he branded me and the activists of our organisation as those of Shibir," Ripon claimed. Bakitair, however, denied to have spoken in favour of Shibir. "The Chhatra League guys insulted me though I did not say anything in Shibir's favour... I said nothing that should be withdrawn. "But I was compelled to apologise with folded hands," the teacher added, fuming. bdnews2
